'''Hops patches''' are used to grow different Hops with the [[Farming]] skill; useful in [[Brewing|brewing]] different types of [[ale]]s with the [[Cooking]] [[skill]]. 4 [[hop seed]]s (only 3 [[Jute seed]]s) are required. Players can pay a nearby farmer to eliminate disease risk; or use varying types of compost and the option to water the patch to reduce (but not eliminate) chance of disease.

Harvesting can yield between 3 and 35 (65 with [[Ultracompost]]) hops. After a hops patch has been harvested, the patch has to be re-planted. Hops on average give less [[experience]] in planting and harvesting than [[allotments]]; however, they are not nearly as susceptible to [[Disease (Farming)|disease]] as allotments. Hops patch do not have a [[compost bin]] nearby but do have a [[Tool leprechaun]].

